## The Crunch You Didn't Bargain For

It seems like Ajinomoto Foods North America Inc. has been a bit too generous with their inclusions lately. On April 1st, they announced multiple Class II recalls due to glass fragments being found in their frozen dumpling and fried rice products. This isn't a small oversight--glass pieces varying up to 3 cm in length are a serious hazard.

Breakdown of products involved:

- Ajinomoto Green Gyoza Vegetable & Edamame Dumplings
- Ling Ling Restaurant Style Fried Rice
- Tai Pei Shrimp Fried Rice
- Trader Joe's Vegetable Fried Rice

Each package had a similar problem: foreign objects posing a risk to consumers. A reminder to check your freezers and think twice before tossing frozen meals into your microwave.

## When Mustard Oil Packs a Punch (Not the Good Kind)

Mangalm LLC has also made headlines this week. Their recent recall involves their 'Tops GOLD' line of pickles, due to potential adulteration with erucic acid in mustard oil--a component of their ingredient list. While mustard oil has a unique flavor profile loved in many cuisines, its inclusion mandates strict regulation to ensure safety.

Brands involved:

- Tops GOLD Stuffed Red Chilli Pickle
- Tops GOLD Mixed Pickle
- Tops GOLD Green Chilli Pickle

The products are imported from India and distributed in the U.S. Be cautious when consuming pickles from this brand.

## Metal is for Machines, Not Cottage Cheese

Albertsons Companies LLC is also in the spotlight after a recall of their Lucerne 2% Cottage Cheese due to metal fragments--specifically, fragments of a stainless steel spring. This is yet another example of how metal contamination continues to disrupt the supply chain and the consumer trust.

## The Recap

Thus far in 2026, we've logged 286 recalls, with 83 of them being Class I--indicating a high risk of serious health consequences. Among the repeat offenders, Ajinomoto Foods North America Inc. has made its presence known with 52 recalls, all being Class I. It seems like some brands need to reprioritize their QA efforts.
